Company Overview of General Reinsurance Corporation



Snapshot People




Company Overview
General Reinsurance Corporation, through its subsidiaries, provides reinsurance services for life and non-life insurance markets in the United States and internationally. It offers reinsurance solutions for aviation, life/health, and programs, as well as treaty and facultative reinsurance solutions. The company also provides risk assessment, transfer, and management services. In addition, it offers asset management, actuarial, life/health product management and consulting, life/health services, and rehabilitation services. General Reinsurance Corporation was incorporated in 1970 and is based in Stamford, Connecticut and has operations in Australia, China, France, Germany, North America, and ...
General Reinsurance Corporation, through its subsidiaries, provides reinsurance services for life and non-life insurance markets in the United States and internationally. It offers reinsurance solutions for aviation, life/health, and programs, as well as treaty and facultative reinsurance solutions. The company also provides risk assessment, transfer, and management services. In addition, it offers asset management, actuarial, life/health product management and consulting, life/health services, and rehabilitation services. General Reinsurance Corporation was incorporated in 1970 and is based in Stamford, Connecticut and has operations in Australia, China, France, Germany, North America, and the United Kingdom. General Reinsurance Corporation operates as a subsidiary of General Re Corporation.
